bio.experienceSummary:
I have many years of experience caring for children of all ages. I am looking to obtain part-time babysitting jobs in the afternoon, evenings and some weekends. I love to teach the children new things, do crafts, explore outside with them and most of all create amazing bonds.
 I want to be able to provide parents with comfort and security of having someone trustworthy watching their little ones.

I absolutely love children. I've worked as a camp counselor, a nanny, and as a teacher at early learning centers. I am a mom and understand the importance of trust and safety when it comes to your child's caregiver. I treat every child I care for as my own and love to introduce them to different experiences, such as music. I've been playing guitar for 20 years and singing for even longer. I also implement the RIE philosophy and Reggio philosophy in my caregiving.

description.displayText:
We've had a number of different nannies for my son (now a little over 2) and Bridget has been by far the most outstanding nanny we've ever had. She is easy to communicate with and extremely professional in how she approaches the job, always punctual if not early, and pitches in so that we can end our work day in a restful home. 

Our son loves her because she patiently reads books to him (even making a good effort on the non-English books!), sings songs, comes up with fun sensory and art activities, and generally treats him respectfully and includes him in all care giving, in line with the RIE philosophy. It really makes a difference in how independent he feels, which benefits all of us.

Our setup was that Bridget would bring her own daughter (4 years old) with her through the summer. The two children had a great time together and if they ever did clash, Bridget always set boundaries fairly and firmly. 

I'm going on maternity leave for a few months but would rehire her in a heartbeat.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Story, and I am a reliable and nurturing caregiver with over 5 years of experience caring for children of all ages. I am passionate about creating safe, fun and engaging environments for kids, whether it's helping with homework, playing games or finding creative ways to be active. I'm also happy to assist with light housekeeping, meal preparation and errands to help make your life a little easier. I am also a pet lover and would be happy to care for them as well. Parents love that I am dependable, responsible, and focused on making every experience positive for their children. I'd love to support your family in any way I can!

I have experience with children through baby sitting and nanny. I have love and compassion for children. I will take care of them like my own children. I will cook, I will clean, l will bathe them if the parents wants me to. I will take them outside and to the park. I will help with homework. I will do grocery and laundry, I will drop them off to school and pick them up from school. I also have my own car. 
I am a very nice person and understanding. I listen and learn new things everyday. You will not regret having me.

description.originalText: Linda is amazing. She goes beyond what you need & my kids loved her! I would definitely use her babysitting services again! Thank you.

bio.experienceSummary:
EXPERIENCED Nanny available for weekends (Friday, Saturday, Sunday). I'm not looking for a steady weekend job, just an "as needed" job.

Mature, responsible, nurturing, flexible, creative and reliable! I have worked with children from 3 months to 16 years old. 

About me: I am a mom to one daughter whom I've raised on my own (her dad/my husband passed away in 2008). She is 25 now. I am a college graduate and worked for 9 years as a paraprofessional (aide for special needs children) with Westfield Board of Education. I've been a full time nanny for 8 years but a before school care and after school care nanny for over 10 years.

description.displayText: Theo is patient and kind and genuinely loves working with babies and children. She is communicative and always accessible and very dependable. She is engaged in the community and prides herself on a fun active and nurturing environment for the kids she cares for. She is resourceful and goes to a extra mile- making baby food from scratch and keeping a detailed diary of feeding and naps.  I feel very confident that my children are safe and well cared for when Theo is watching them

bio.experienceSummary: The child I am with will be starting full-time school shortly. Ideally searching for a newborn/infant, as I am looking for longevity. I was also a PreK teacher in Metuchen for 4 years and a teacher's aide in the Edison school system for 17 years. I have nannied for over 10 years for 4 amazing families whose children have since started school. I'm a proud mom of 3 adult, well-rounded, successful children. I've also babysat for many families in the area. I am CPR and First Aide certified, Also, in my free time, I cook and deliver meals to several families in Metuchen.

description.originalText: If I could give more than 5 stars, I would. Tina is amazing. She is loving, caring and completely reliable. After taking care of our daughter for the past 2 years she’s now a member of our family. The next family that she works for will be so lucky.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a experienced loving childcare provider, and mother having 20 years of experience, not including raising my own two children (now 23 and 25 years old). Caring for and teaching children has always been my passion. I treat every child as if they were my own. I have worked as a nanny for multiple families, staying with each for three years or more, as well as working in preschools and daycares.

I provide engaging activities throughout the day, including coloring, reading, singing, and developmental play. My childcare includes teaching important milestones such as crawling, sitting up, walking, talking, and potty training. Weather permitting, I love to take children outside for walks, park visits, etc.

My experience includes caring for infants through elementary-aged children, which also includes twins and children with special needs. I provide patience, and loving care for each child's unique needs. I have excellent references from families I provided loving care for.

I'd describe my personality as respectful, kind and lovely person

I like working with children and seniors because I always love to help them. As a child I care of them as they are my family.

I specially love to care infants or toddlers because first Is true that parents need support and second because they are so sweet. Since I am with my couple we try to have one but unfortunately we can't so caring babies is like come true my dream.

I have experience improving their skills, napping time, changing diapers and making bottles. 

It is so proud to see how kid start to grow and understand the things. It is an amazing experience 

I would love to work with you

I am 39 years old. I have nearly 15 years of daycare work experience-working with children ranging from 6 weeks to 6 years old. I also have 10 years of nanny work experience. I am a non-smoker. I have a clean driving record. I was First Aid and CPR trained for infants, children and adults and can renew it if needed. I love the outdoors, playing games and reading books. Arts and crafts are my specialty.

As a nurturing caregiver with nine years of experience, my passion lies in positively shaping young lives. I am patient, creative, and approachable, and I strive to create a safe and stimulating environment for children.

I believe in open communication with parents and regularly provide updates on their child's day. I adapt to each family's unique rules and routines to ensure consistency for the children in my care.

I enjoy a variety of games with kids, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational activities. My college education and CPR training further enhance my ability to provide quality care. I'm comfortable caring for up to three children of all ages.

Whether it's cooking meals, helping with carpools, or engaging in fun activities, I'm here to support families and bring joy to the children I care for. It would be my pleasure to be a part of your family's journey.

description.originalText: Melisa was an amazing nanny to my 3 yearold and 6 yearold sons. She took great care of them and was always on time for school dropoffs and pickups. She kept my younger child engaged with fun activities and helped my older one with schoolwork. Her kindness, reliability, and genuine care made us feel at ease, knowing our children were in great hands. I highly recommend Melisa to any family.
